-{"id":"br-97gc6.3.1","title":"Blockers: diagnose br doctor WAL/SHM anomaly and preserved recovery artifacts","description":"Investigate the current br doctor warnings about preserved recovery artifacts and a WAL sidecar without matching SHM. Determine whether this is stale debris, a real consistency risk, or a benign leftover; record a safe remediation path without destructive cleanup.","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:10:16.206282160Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["beads","db","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1260,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-18: the live anomaly is specific to .beads/beads.db-wal existing without .beads/beads.db-shm. After the long-running br writer exited, lsof showed no remaining open handles on beads.db or beads.db-wal, but the WAL file still persisted. Preserved recovery artifacts are separate from that live complaint: .beads/.br_recovery contains beads.db.20260313_224031_514673114.bak and beads.db-wal.orphan_20260313T224229Z, while the repo root also contains historical beads.db.bad_*, beads.db.rebuild_*, vacuum/reindex test files, and recovery_20260313T224002Z.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:48Z"},{"id":1265,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-19: `am macros start-session` initially failed in `/data/projects/mcp_agent_mail_rust` because repo-local `./storage.sqlite3` was malformed and had a stale `storage.sqlite3-wal` sidecar without a live repo-local holder. `lsof storage.sqlite3 storage.sqlite3-wal` in the repo showed no open handles. The unhealthy listener on port 8765 is a separate process (`/home/ubuntu/.local/bin/am`, pid 3943291, cwd `/home/ubuntu`) holding `/home/ubuntu/storage.sqlite3` and `/home/ubuntu/storage.sqlite3-wal`, so it is not the writer for the repo-local DB. Safe non-destructive remediation for the repo-local mailbox DB was: 1) verify no repo-local open handles, 2) run `AM_INTERFACE_MODE=cli am doctor reconstruct --dry-run --json`, 3) run `AM_INTERFACE_MODE=cli am doctor reconstruct --yes --json`. That quarantined the corrupt DB to `storage.sqlite3.corrupt-*` artifacts and rebuilt a fresh `./storage.sqlite3` from the Git mailbox archive, after which `am doctor check` reported the DB accessible and I could register as `TopazIbis`. Residual findings after reconstruct: archive/db parity still fails (`messages archive=1951 db=1292`), `schema_version` is `user_version = 0`, the archive contains duplicate canonical message ids and missing `project.json` files for some archived projects, and the repo now has preserved `storage.sqlite3*.corrupt-*` / salvage artifacts by design rather than active live-state debris. Separate but related tracker evidence: `.beads/beads.db-wal` still exists without `.beads/beads.db-shm`, `br doctor` still reports that anomaly, and `br update` for this bead persisted the status change to `in_progress` but returned `UNIQUE constraint failed: blocked_issues_cache.issue_id`, so Beads mutation reporting needs separate follow-up.","created_at":"2026-03-19T17:47:01Z"},{"id":1268,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Patched `crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs` to handle the critical mailbox split where `am mail inbox` could fail with `Resource temporarily busy` while robot reads still succeeded. The fix adds a minimal inbox-read schema probe, a best-effort direct SQLite fallback for mailbox reads, routes `mail inbox` through that fallback when the async pool/init path reports a transient busy error, and covers the read-path with new CLI tests. Remote verification is running through `rch`; one unrelated pre-existing async-closure lifetime issue in `get_project_record()` had to be flattened first so the crate could compile. Attempted to notify other agents via Agent Mail, but the live server on `127.0.0.1:8765` still rejects `TopazIbis` because it is pointed at a different mailbox DB than the repaired repo-local one.","created_at":"2026-03-19T18:10:16Z"}]}
