osure lifetime issue in `get_project_record()` had to be flattened first so the crate could compile. Attempted to notify other agents via Agent Mail, but the live server on `127.0.0.1:8765` still rejects `TopazIbis` because it is pointed at a different mailbox DB than the repaired repo-local one.","created_at":"2026-03-19T18:10:16Z"},{"id":1269,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Fresh-eyes follow-up on the mailbox fallback patch uncovered two more real issues in `crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs`: (1) `check_inbox_direct()` was still using a weaker manual project lookup than the new direct inbox path, so it now reuses `context::resolve_project()`; (2) the fallback trigger initially missed real DB-layer variants (`Resource temporarily busy` / raw `database is busy`) and then became too broad, so `is_resource_busy_cli_error()` is now narrowed to transient busy/lock forms only. Added unit coverage for the accepted busy variants and a negative assertion for non-transient `disk i/o error`.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:23:14Z"},{"id":1270,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Fresh-eyes pass: fixed another inbox fallback hole in crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/lib.rs. classify_server_tool_call/server_tool_error_is_unavailable now treats HTTP 5xx from the MCP server as unavailable rather than hard rejection, so am mail inbox can still fall back to the local DB path when the server is unhealthy. Added tests covering 5xx fallback and preserving 4xx rejection semantics. Re-running rch cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-cli --tests; expected remaining blocker is still the unrelated upstream sqlmodel-frankensqlite compile failure.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:31:14Z"}]}
