+{"id":"br-aazao.1","title":"Verification Coverage 1.1: repo-wide audit of test realism, gaps, and ownership","description":"# Verification Coverage 1.1: Repo-Wide Audit of Test Realism, Gaps, and Ownership\n\n## Why\nBefore adding more tests, the project needs an explicit inventory of what is already covered, how that coverage is achieved, and where confidence is artificially inflated by substitutes, wrappers, or fixture-only paths.\n\n## Deliverables\n- enumerate the workspace by crate, major module cluster, and critical workflow surface\n- map each surface to existing unit, property, integration, conformance, and E2E coverage\n- classify each test by realism grade:\n  - real-path / real dependency\n  - deterministic local fixture\n  - sanctioned substitute\n  - mock / fake / stub\n  - untested\n- identify which tests are merely contract or formatting tests versus true behavioral tests\n- identify ownership / expected home for missing tests so the backlog is implementable\n- produce a prioritized gap ledger that distinguishes critical-path gaps from cosmetic gaps\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- future beads can point back to this issue as the canonical inventory rather than rediscovering the current state\n- the audit explicitly calls out present realism exceptions such as stub encoders, stub embedders, stub LLM completions, mock installer artifacts, and fake filesystem/repo state tests\n- the audit is specific enough to drive per-subsystem implementation work without hand-wavy “add more tests” follow-ups\n\n## Important Notes\nThis is not a paper exercise. The output must be actionable enough that later beads can close gaps mechanically.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-18T13:51:02.997462159Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:21:27.349181304Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:21:27.348483236Z","close_reason":"Completed canonical verification coverage ledger covering crate-cluster inventory, E2E suite topology, and realism/ownership mapping in docs/VERIFICATION_COVERAGE_LEDGER.md","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["coverage","e2e","repo-wide","testing","unit-tests","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-aazao.1","depends_on_id":"br-aazao","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T13:51:02.997462159Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-aazao.1.1","title":"Verification Coverage 1.1.1: inventory unit, integration, and conformance coverage by crate cluster","description":"# Verification Coverage 1.1.1: Inventory Unit, Integration, and Conformance Coverage by Crate Cluster\n\n## Why\nA usable audit starts with an explicit map of implementation surfaces to existing nearby tests. Without that map, the rest of the verification effort becomes intuition-driven and repetitive.\n\n## Deliverables\n- enumerate crates and major internal module clusters\n- record nearby unit, integration, property, and conformance tests for each cluster\n- separate direct behavioral tests from formatting/contract-only checks\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- later coverage-closure work can point to one inventory instead of rediscovering the current state\n- every major crate cluster has an explicit current-state line item","notes":"Started after bv robot triage. Building the canonical crate-cluster inventory of unit, integration, conformance, and E2E coverage; will publish a ledger doc under docs/ and use it as the reference for the follow-on verification beads.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-03-18T14:00:59.526448380Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","updated_at":"2026-03-19T00:07:26.904995225Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T00:07:26.904458460Z","close_reason":"Completed: published docs/VERIFICATION_COVERAGE_LEDGER.md as the canonical crate-cluster inventory of inline, integration, conformance, and confidence-profile coverage.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","coverage","testing","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-aazao.1.1","depends_on_id":"br-aazao.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T14:00:59.526448380Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-aazao.1.2","title":"Verification Coverage 1.1.2: inventory E2E suites, harness richness, and artifact gaps","description":"# Verification Coverage 1.1.2: Inventory E2E Suites, Harness Richness, and Artifact Gaps\n\n## Why\nThe repository has many E2E entrypoints, but the suite surface is large enough that overlap and omissions are easy to miss unless the scripts and shared harness are mapped explicitly.\n\n## Deliverables\n- enumerate every direct and wrapper E2E entrypoint\n- record what transport, workflow, or failure family each suite covers\n- record current logging/artifact richness and obvious blind spots\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- later E2E matrix work can start from a concrete coverage ledger rather than anecdote\n- wrapper suites and thin scripts are clearly distinguished from richly instrumented suites","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-03-18T14:01:20.944797312Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:09:03.361098750Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:09:03.360286721Z","close_reason":"Completed E2E suite inventory, harness richness, and artifact-gap ledger in docs/VERIFICATION_COVERAGE_LEDGER.md","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","e2e","logging","testing","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-aazao.1.2","depends_on_id":"br-aazao.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T14:01:20.944797312Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-aazao.1.3","title":"Verification Coverage 1.1.3: build realism-grade ledger and ownership map","description":"# Verification Coverage 1.1.3: Build Realism-Grade Ledger and Ownership Map\n\n## Why\nThe audit only becomes actionable once every important gap is tied to a realism grade and an obvious home for the follow-up work.\n\n## Deliverables\n- assign realism grades to the inventoried tests\n- mark critical-path gaps separately from cosmetic gaps\n- record the expected owner or subsystem for each missing lane\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- the gap ledger is prioritized and assignable rather than just descriptive\n- later burn-down and sign-off beads can reuse the same realism ledger directly","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-03-18T14:01:32.890009820Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:20:47.716304938Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:20:47.715358765Z","close_reason":"Completed realism-grade and ownership ledger in docs/VERIFICATION_COVERAGE_LEDGER.md","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","coverage","ownership","testing","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-aazao.1.3","depends_on_id":"br-aazao.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T14:01:32.890009820Z","created_by":"CrimsonSnow","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
